<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,152,990]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,504,422,448]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—This new species is known from the 
<typeStatus box="[974,1024,422,448]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">type</typeStatus>
locality only, where it grows as an epiphyte in the understory of the Atlantic Forest of Santa Teresa, an area known for its high botanical diversity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
